## Phase 1: Tier 1 integrations (existing MCPs)

Install and configure each MCP server listed in
`integrations/existing/`. Verify each smoke-tests successfully.

For each tool:
- [ ] Read `integrations/existing/<tool>.md`
- [ ] Install per the file's instructions
- [ ] Configure auth (API key / OAuth) per `governance/credentials.md`
- [ ] Add to `.mcp.json` (Claude Code) or equivalent registry in your tool
- [ ] Smoke test: invoke a read-only operation
- [ ] Document any deviations in this checklist

{{tier_1_tool_checklist}}

## Phase 2: Tier 2 integrations (custom MCP wrappers)

For each tool in `integrations/needs-mcp-wrapper/`, run the
`mcp-builder` skill (Claude Code) per the tool's `BUILD.md`.

For each tool:
- [ ] Read `integrations/needs-mcp-wrapper/<tool>/BUILD.md`
- [ ] Verify `openapi.yaml` validates: `swagger-cli validate openapi.yaml`
- [ ] Run `mcp-builder` with the endpoint subset in `ENDPOINTS.md`
- [ ] Smoke test the generated wrapper
- [ ] Add to `.mcp.json`

{{tier_2_tool_checklist}}

## Phase 3: Tier 3+4 integrations (n8n flows + webhook receivers)

Tier 3 (n8n flows) and Tier 4 (webhook receivers) can run in parallel.

n8n flows — for each in `integrations/needs-n8n-flow/`:
- [ ] Install n8n (self-hosted Docker or n8n.cloud) if not already
- [ ] Import `<flow-id>-flow.json`
- [ ] Fill in credentials per the sticky notes
- [ ] Wire to AgentBloc inbox (HTTP Request node → wake.sh webhook)
- [ ] Test + activate

Webhook receivers — for each in `integrations/needs-webhook/`:
- [ ] Read `<tool>-receiver.md` design spec
- [ ] Implement the HTTP endpoint (bash + nc, Python, Node, etc.)
- [ ] Implement signature verification per the spec
- [ ] Implement idempotency per the spec
- [ ] Register the URL with the vendor + verify with their test mechanism

{{tier_3_4_tool_checklist}}

## Phase 4: Workflows + agents

Now wire the agent prompts to the integrations.

For each agent in `agents/`:
- [ ] Read `agents/<id>/role.md` (CrewAI-shaped role + goal)
- [ ] Read `agents/<id>/prompts.md` (system + wake prompt reference)
- [ ] Read `agents/<id>/tools.md` (tool list with cross-links)
- [ ] Read `agents/<id>/blast-radius.md` (autonomy + risk envelope)
- [ ] Implement the wake.md (the reference impl shows how)
- [ ] Wire tools from `tools.md` to integrations from earlier phases

For each workflow in `workflows/`:
- [ ] Verify all referenced agents exist in `agents/`
- [ ] Verify the trigger source is implemented (cron / webhook / event /
      inter-agent)
- [ ] Implement the success-criteria assertions as integration tests

{{workflow_checklist}}

## Phase 5: Runtime substrate

Pick the runtime per `runtime/BUILD.md` + `runtime/alternatives.md`.

If using the bash + cron reference impl:
- [ ] `cp runtime/reference-impl/.env.example .env` and fill in
- [ ] `./runtime/reference-impl/cron-generator.sh apply` (or set
      `AGENTBLOC_NO_CRON=1` for foreground)
- [ ] Verify cron lines installed: `crontab -l`
- [ ] Wire hooks: copy `runtime/reference-impl/hooks/` to `hooks/` and
      register in `.claude/settings.local.json`
- [ ] Smoke test: trigger one wake manually and verify it completes

If using a different runtime:
- [ ] See `runtime/alternatives.md` for the chosen option
- [ ] Implement the equivalent of: cron / inbox handoff / approval
      check / audit emission / cost capture

## Phase 6: Test + ship

- [ ] Each workflow's success criteria pass as automated tests
- [ ] `governance/blast-radius.md` enforcement verified (try invoking
      a forbidden tool and confirm it's blocked)
- [ ] `governance/audit-trail.md` schema validated against real audit
      output
- [ ] `governance/pii-redaction.md` sample inputs redact correctly
- [ ] `governance/kill-switch.md` halt mechanism tested end-to-end
- [ ] `governance/approval-protocol.md` round-trip tested with real
      operator
- [ ] One full happy-path workflow run completes end-to-end
- [ ] One failure-mode run produces correct escalation
- [ ] Documentation updated (any deviations from this spec are noted)

